“Space exploration is a force of nature unto itself that no other force in society can rival.” -Neil deGrasse Tyson.
ISRO, The Indian Space Research Organization is an institution with unmatched reputation in the country for its successful missions and contributions to the nation. It is instrumental in catapulting India into the elite club of global space research. The secrets of space have been unraveled and made within reach by ISRO.
The exhibition will showcase models of various projects of ISRO which include The Polar Satellite Launch Vehicle PSLV, The Geosynchronous Satellite Launch Vehicle (GSLV), the Chandrayaan-1, India’s first lunar mission. Models of different satellites, their components, the working principles will also be exhibited.

